Information for the database:

Filter: takes as arguments name of the table, array of column names, array of comparison signs and array of values. 
Each group of i-th elements from the arrays makes a filter. Returns a record.

SelectAll: no arguments, returns array of the records

SelectById: takes as argument id, returns a record

Insert: takes as agruments an non-associative array 
Template for a room: name, language, difficulty, timeLimit, minPlayers, maxPlayers, imageURL; 
Template for a riddle: language, type(enum), task, solution, language, imageURL;
Types of riddles are: “numeric”, “colors”, “shapes”, “rebus”, “directions”, “sorting”, “trivia”, “other”;

There are examples for everything in the main function.
